children.text:
Instructions:
1. Sit upright on the chair, with your left hand holding on the seat back. Then set your right hand to the lateral side of your left thigh.
2. Inhale and clasp the seat back; exhale and turn your upper body leftward and backward to the utmost. Here maintain for 3 deep breaths.
3. Return and repeat the same movement by the other side.
4. Relax your upper body when practicing, your lower limbs kept still.

Functions:
1. Helps provide a better blood circulation; alleviates waist pains and backaches.
2. Also prevents constipation.
Support your chin with hands to stretch your neck…
Do a simple massage on your neck to relieve your stress…
Bend your upper body laterally to stretch your waist…
Twist your body for a better blood circulation…
Bend down like a traingle for total refreshment…
